column14: 50,000 cells were washed in ice cold 1X PBS and re-suspended in 50 μl ice cold lysis buffer. Then nuclei were pelleted at 500 x g for 10 min at 40C. The pellet was then incubated with the transposition reaction mix for 30 min at 37°C and then purified using the MinElute PCR Purification kit (Qiagen, Hilden, Germany).
column15: Base calling and demultiplexing were processed using CASAVA version 1.8, Reads were mapped using BWA-MEM to the 1000 Genomes (b37) build of the human genome reference., Peaks were called using MACS2 with options BAMPE and -q, Bigwig files were generated using bedGraphTobBgWig.
